The paper proposes a method for interactive boundary extraction using a deep, patch-based representation and an active contour framework. This involves training a class-specific convolutional neural network, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The evaluation of the proposed method on medical and non-medical challenge data sets suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
